The Commission of Inquiry into State Capture continues on Thursday where Deputy Chief Justice, Raymond Zondo, is expected to hear applications from a number of individuals who want to testify or cross examine witnesses. Amongst those who are expected to apply is Congress of the People (COPE) spokesperson, Dennis Bloem, who laid a charge to the police following reports of former African National Congress (ANC) Member of Parliament (MP) Vytjie Mentor being offered a cabinet post by the Gupta family. Former Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) boss, Mzwanele Manyi, testified on Wednesday and will be questioned by the commission on November 23. Watch related videos below:  